<TITLE> No new 'tax holidays': finmin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)  The finance minister on Tuesday said that the government will not provide any new "tax holidays" for nascent industries. Minister MA Muhith was speaking to journalists following a meeting with representatives of Dhaka's Metropolitan Chamber of Commerce and Industries (MCCI) and International Monetary Fund (IMF). MCCI representatives had asked that the current tax breaks be extended for another next five years. Muhith told journalists that, "Tax has to be paid even if it is only a little." At the meeting, the MCCI had asked that he allowed 'captive power plants' to distribute their surplus electricity commercially to other companies or householders. Muhith said that he had told MCCI that he "could not say any thing on this right now. There are questions about what should be the price for the energy." The finance minister also added that he had requested assistance from the IMF to implement the country's 'Poverty Reduction Strategy Paper.' b
